{"TAKE":[{"def":"In an active sense; To lay hold of; to seize with the hands, or otherwise; to grasp; to get into one's hold or possession; to procure; to seize and carry away; to convey.","pos":""},{"def":"In a somewhat passive sense, to receive; to bear; to endure; to acknowledge; to accept.","pos":""}],"TAKE-IN":[{"def":"Imposition; fraud.","pos":""}],"TAKE-OFF":[{"def":"An imitation, especially in the way of caricature.","pos":""}],"TAKE-UP":[{"def":"That which takes up or tightens; specifically, a device in a sewing machine for drawing up the slack thread as the needle rises, in completing a stitch.","pos":""}],"TAKER":[{"def":"One who takes or receives; one who catches or apprehended.","pos":""}],"TAKING":[{"def":"Apt to take; alluring; attracting.","pos":""},{"def":"Infectious; contageous.","pos":""}],"TAKING-OFF":[{"def":"Removal; murder.","pos":""}]}